    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-05-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-05-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="79" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d79">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1986.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1867-05-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 20, 1867</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of the 2d of May, No. 1361,
                            has been received. There is no reason why you should not give Lord
                            Stanley a full copy of my despatch No. 1965.</p>
                <pb facs="0161" n="93" xml:id="pg_93"/>
                <p>My confidential despatch of May 2d, No. 1971, will have removed from your
                            mind any impression that the President may be expected to accede to the
                            limitation upon the arbitration of the Alabama claims which Lord Stanley
                            proposed.</p>
                <p>The United States are thus in the attitude of insisting upon the claims,
                            as they have consistently done from the beginning, and of declining to
                            accede to arbitration thereupon with limitations hitherto insisted upon
                            by her Majesty’s government.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
